The national secretariat of the ruling APC has been put on lockdown by IGP Mohammed Adamu.
Armed police officers are guarding the building now in the run-up to a meeting the splinters of the party’s national working committee slated for Tuesday.
Armed Police personnel sealed the National Secretariat of the All Progressives Congress on the orders of the Inspector General of Police, Mohammed Adamu, on Tuesday.
Following the court order that suspended the party’s national chairman Adams Oshiomhole, three chairmen—Abila Ajimobi, Victor Giadom, and Hillard Eta – have emerged through a lot of intrigues and maneuvering.
Oshimhole has since be reinstated by his ward in Etsako, and Giadom has been suspended by his home state (Rivers) chapter of the APC.